From c1cb10a14a25f951b320e86c6cec48822da35b78 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Balamurugan Ramar <quic_bramar@quicinc.com>
Date: Thu, 10 Apr 2025 23:27:14 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] mac80211: UPSTREAMDPwifi Fix KW issue rx->sta dereferenced 
 without  checking for null condition

In the function __ieee80211_rx_h_amsdu(), the rx->sta pointer is
dereferenced without verifying if it is NULL, even though it can be
NULL as indicated by a previous condition check.

Hence to fix this, check rx->sta is not NULL before proceeding with
the next condition.

patch-dependency: none

Signed-off-by: Sarika Sharma <quic_sarishar@quicinc.com>
Signed-off-by: Balamurugan Ramar <quic_bramar@quicinc.com>
---
 net/mac80211/rx.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/net/mac80211/rx.c b/net/mac80211/rx.c
index 870a0a3..be14c31 100644
--- a/net/mac80211/rx.c
+++ b/net/mac80211/rx.c
@@ -3186,7 +3186,7 @@ __ieee80211_rx_h_amsdu(struct ieee80211_rx_data *rx, u8 data_offset)
 					  data_offset, true))
 		return RX_DROP_U_BAD_AMSDU;
 
-	if (rx->sta->amsdu_mesh_control < 0) {
+	if (rx->sta && rx->sta->amsdu_mesh_control < 0) {
 		s8 valid = -1;
 		int i;
 
-- 
2.34.1

